President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation declaring June 2017 as Great Outdoors Month in the United States. The proclamation encourages Americans to take advantage of the summer season by enjoying the beauty and adventure of the nation's lakes, mountains, forests, and even their own backyards. It emphasizes the importance of preserving and cherishing outdoor spaces for future generations and highlights the cultural and historic significance of these areas. President Trump also mentions his efforts to improve the management of public lands through public-private partnerships. He urges all Americans to explore the great outdoors and act as stewards of the environment.